  "prompt": "How can I forgive what I can't forget?",
  "response": "Forgiving something you can't forget is challenging, but here are some strategies that might help:\n\n1. Understand forgiveness\n- Forgiveness is for you, not the other person\n- It doesn't mean forgetting or condoning what happened\n- It means releasing the emotional burden for your own peace\n\n2. Emotional processing\n- Acknowledge your feelings\n- Allow yourself to grieve\n- Consider therapy or counseling\n- Practice self-compassion\n\n3. Shift your perspective\n- Try to understand the context\n- Recognize the humanity in the person who hurt you\n- Focus on your personal growth\n- See the experience as a lesson\n\n4. Practical techniques\n- Write a letter (don't necessarily send it)\n- Practice meditation\n- Use positive affirmations\n- Journal about your feelings\n\n5. Gradual approach\n- Forgiveness is a process, not an instant event\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Take small steps\n- Accept that healing takes time\n\n6. Set boundaries\n- Protect yourself from further harm\n- Learn from past experiences\n- Create a safe emotional environment\n\nRemember, forgiving doesn't mean you have to reconcile or continue a relationship. It's about finding inner peace and moving forward.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
